Dynamic KDB+ FastMCP Server

Connects to a KDB+/Q instance, introspects available functions,
and dynamically registers each as a FastMCP tool with rich docstrings,
parameter schemas, and a server-level prompt describing purpose and usage.

Usage:
python kdb_mcp_server.py –host localhost –port 5000 [–user kdb] [–password secret]

Environment variables (override CLI args):
KDB_HOST, KDB_PORT, KDB_USER, KDB_PASSWORD
